    <note>Ling(1) Ce [1176] Used the jinshi to establish his family (qijia) branch of the lineage. He was strong in administrative expertise (qianggan). The linkage with the Suzhou Ling is established though his descendant, Zhen [15085] (CBD, 3, 1728), who has the same generational name as Kui's [15083] grandnephew. Since Ce served in finance during Ding(1) Wei's [1641] tenure as Finance commissioner, I am assuming that Xian, a Suzhou 992 jinshi, was a brother who moved to Suzhou and that Minshi [15079] is a grandnephew and that Xian is Minshi's grandfather. XCB, 53.8b, 76.2a; Guangxi TZ, 16.4a; Guangdong TZ, 14.21a; SS, 307.12a-12b. CBD, 3, 1728.</note>
